title: TU Power Poll: Columbia moves into top three after big win
text:
TU Power Poll: Columbia moves into top three after big win 
Thu, Oct 15, 2015 @ 9:43 pm | updated Thu, Oct 15, 2015 @ 10:26 pm Photos BOB MACK/Florida Times-Union Columbia SS Kenny Johnson cuts back after intercepting a pass from Bolles QB Mac Jones at 3:26 in the second quarter as RB Isaiah Westbrook (26) tries to make the tackle. Johnson scored a touchdown on the play. 
POWER POLL 
Last week’s rankings in parentheses. All games 7 p.m. Friday unless indicated 
1. (1) TRINITY CHRISTIAN (6-0), CLASS 3A 
Last week: d. Tallahassee Godby, 56-31 
This week: Duval Charter (0-6), 7:30 
Glance: There are few challenges remaining for the Conquerors to deliver a 10-0 season. The Panthers on homecoming could be the area’s biggest mismatch of the season. 
2. (3) RAINES (6-0), CLASS 4A 
Last week: d. First Coast, 26-15 
This week: Jackson (0-6), Saturday, 2 p.m. 
Glance: While they were never really in trouble, the Vikings struggled with execution throughout their win over the Buccaneers last week. 
3. (9) COLUMBIA (5-1), CLASS 7A 
Last week: d. Bolles, 49-20 
This week: Atlantic Coast (4-3) 
Glance: A 29-point win on the road over the No. 1 team in Class 4A sends the Tigers up into the top three. 
4. (4) ST. AUGUSTINE (6-0), CLASS 6A 
Last week: Off 
This week: at White (2-4) 
Glance: The Yellow Jackets lost to White in the regional semifinals last season, although the roles should be reversed this time around. A win would be the 50th consecutive district victory for St. Augustine. 
5. (2) BOLLES (6-1), CLASS 4A 
Last week: L. to Columbia, 49-20 
This week: at Port Orange Atlantic (0-6), 3:30 
Glance: The Bulldogs lost the battle on both lines in one of their worst regular season home losses ever. The good news is that it’s an easy road up until Oct. 29 at Raines. 
6. (5) MANDARIN (6-0), CLASS 8A 
Last week: d. Wolfson, 54-6 
This week: at Sandalwood (6-1) 
Glance: Major district title implications on the line at the Saints. A victory here puts Mandarin in the driver’s seat in District 1-8A. 
7. (6) UNIVERSITY CHRISTIAN (5-1), CLASS 2A 
Last week: d. Eagle’s View, 76-0 
This week: Cedar Creek Christian (5-1), 7:30 
Glance: The Christians will clinch the District 2-2A title with a victory over the Saints in what could be UC’s biggest challenge since Sept. 11 against Trinity. 
8. (8) OAKLEAF (5-1), CLASS 7A 
Last week : Off 
This week: Arlington CD (0-5) 
Glance: Oakleaf’s major goal this week is staying healthy. The Knights are concentrating on two big games — Oct. 23 at Creekside and Oct. 30 at Bartram Trail. 
9. (10) UNION COUNTY (6-0), CLASS 1A 
Last week: d. Hawthorne, 36-18 
This week: at Fort White (4-2), 7:30 
Glance: The Tigers took a big step toward a District 6-1A crown last week. They can nail it down with a win on the road over the Indians. 
10. (7) SANDALWOOD (6-1), CLASS 8A 
Last week: l. to Lee, 14-7 
This week: Mandarin (6-0) 
Glance: The Saints hang on in the Power Poll after a painful offensive effort last week. 

On the bubble: Bartram Trail (5-2, Class 7A).
